== Dependencies ==

Download and build SnakeYAML (the latest release has bugs in; you need the
latest development version):

  $EXT$ hg clone https://snakeyaml.googlecode.com/hg/ snakeyaml
  $EXT/snakeyaml$ mvn package
  plugin-Interdex/lib$ ln -s $EXT/snakeyaml/target/SnakeYAML-1.3-SNAPSHOT.jar

Download the latest google-collections (I will probably remove this at some
point since the only class that uses it is probably going to be unnecessary.):

  $EXT$ wget "http://google-collections.googlecode.com/files/google-collect-1.0-rc2.zip"
  $EXT$ unzip google-collect-1.0-rc2.zip
  plugin-Interdex/lib$ ln -s $EXT/google-collect-1.0-rc2/google-collect-1.0-rc2.jar

Download and build bliki-doclet, which is a little something I cooked up to
have mediawiki markup instead of ugly HTML in javadoc comments:

  $EXT$ git clone http://infinity0.ath.cx/s/bliki-doclet/.git/
  $EXT$ wget "http://gwtwiki.googlecode.com/files/bliki.3.0.12.zip"
  $EXT$ unzip bliki.3.0.12.zip
  $EXT/bliki-doclet/lib$ ln -s ../../info.bliki.wiki/bliki-core-3.0.12-SNAPSHOT.jar
  $EXT/bliki-doclet$ ./mksrc.sh src.orig/openjdk-6-src-b16-24_apr_2009/ && ant
  plugin-Interdex/lib$ ln -s $EXT/bliki-doclet/dist/bliki-doclet*.jar bliki-doclet.jar

(If you don't care about generating pretty javadocs, you can comment out the
line that starts "<doclet" in build.xml, to make the build process not fail.)

== Build ==

Build and generate javadocs:

  plugin-Interdex$ ant

Compile, test and package only:

  plugin-Interdex$ ant jar
